      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "LINDEN BOOTS (7) jumped from a middle draw last time and could manage only fourth and beaten 4.5 lengths (17.09) at this track. Better than last start and worth following up. EZARD DASH (2) was midfield throughout and finished there last time when 5th (22.91) at Shepparton. Has never been out of the placings from two starts out of this box. Will give the top chances plenty to think about. MISS DUDDLES (1) was narrowly beaten last time, jumping from this same box when a 0.8 lengths second in a Maiden over 400m at Geelong. Key chance on best form. LITTLE SPLINTER (8) can finish much closer after missing a cheque at this track last start.",
